node.text:
No better feeling than being able to do what you love where ever whenever. 
Forever grateful for my athletic background as gymnastics has provided me with a multitude of life skills and lessons. 
I love what I do as an athlete and as a trainer and am so fortunate I’m able to share my passion with my clients, followers, and friends. 

Shoutout to @toro_films film for creating this amazing video. Always an honour to get to work with one of the best in the industry. 

Top: @gymsharkwomen @gymshark 
Bottoms: @ryderwear @ryderwearwomen

node.text:
❕Skill Drill Saturday❕

Single leg stability & Strength - New Program Releasing this month on my app! 

1) 3 point reaches: This drill can be done on flat ground/bosu ball in order to help improve single leg strength and stability. Aim to reach as far as you can in each position while being able to maintain balance 

2) Alt Cossack squats: Staying as low as you can through the transition from side to side. Aim to have equal ROM on both sides. 

3) Single leg deadlift to pistol squat: Focus on squeezing your core through both transitions from deadlift to pistol and pistol to standing. 

@gymshark @gymsharkwomen - New @whitneyysimmons V3 releasing next Thursday 2pm EST!

node.text:
Been a while so I thought I’d share some fun facts! 🥰

Serious: 
1) My go to Starbucks order: shaken espresso with oat milk & toffee nut syrup 
2) Bulgarian lunges are my favourite lower body exercise 
3) Voice notes are my fave and I always try to keep them under 30 seconds

Silly: 
1) I count to three using rock star hands 🤟🏻
2) Took me an entire season to realize Money Heist was dubbed in English 
3) I like the sound a vacuum makes when it picks up dirt 

Now you know a little more about me 😋
